headline: Tech Highfliers Slide. 3 Stocks Whose Charts Point to Turnaround.
summary: Palo Alto Networks  a software-focused cybersecurity company, is turning in a very mediocre 2025.  The stock is flat year to date and now sits 19% off its most recent 52-week high, a clear display of relative weakness with the  just 11% off its own annual peak.  Palo Alto shares have slumped more than 10% this week alone and are on track to log their first three-week losing streak since April.
